<!--- Guidance for high_priorityGuidance --->
<ul>

	<li>High Priority courses are those for which alternative teaching methods will be most important if disaster strikes &ndash; whether the disaster be pervasive (flood, earthquake, pandemic) or local (illness of an instructor).</li>

	<li><strong>Course Number & Title</strong>. Use the official course numbers and titles displayed in the campus&acute;s Course Catalog.  In the number, include any coded names, prefixes & suffixes as appropriate &ndash; e.g. CHEM 1A or COMPSCI 61B.</li>
	<li><strong>Course-casting</strong>.  The term &ldquo;course-casting&rdquo; encompasses all technologies used for audio or video recording and dissemination of classes &ndash; webcasting, podcasting, YouTube, etc.</li>
    <li>Relevant documents can be uploaded on the <a
		href="./getKeyResourcesDocuments">Document Summary</a> screen.</li>
    <li>See the <a href="./toKnowItems">Things To Know</a> screen for further context.</li>

</ul>
